üéØ Overview

NREACH is an automated attendance notification system that sends customized attendance updates directly to parents. All communication and actions are fully trackable and controlled by the admin.

üèóÔ∏è Purpose
Improve parent awareness of student attendance
Reduce manual calls/messages by staff
Enable real-time attendance communication

‚ú® Key Features
üìä Attendance Tracking
Daily, weekly, or monthly attendance monitoring
Real-time attendance updates
Multi-class support

üîî Automated Parent Notifications
Attendance alerts sent via SMS / Email
Customizable notification templates
Scheduled and triggered notifications

‚öôÔ∏è Admin Customization
Configure attendance thresholds (low attendance alerts)
Choose message formats and schedules
Manage user roles and permissions

üìà Full Traceability
Complete logs of all sent messages
Delivery status tracking
Audit trail for all actions

üë• Roles
Operator
HOD
Parents/Students
	
üõ† Tech Stack
Backend
Runtime: Node.js v16+
Framework: Express.js v4.x
Database: Oracle Database 19c+
ORM: oracledb package
Authentication: JWT + bcrypt

Frontend
Framework: React.js
UI Library: Bootstrap
HTTP Client: Axios

External Services
SMS/Notifications: Twilio API
Package Manager: npm/yarn
Environment: dotenv

üìö APIs

1) Authentication
2) SMS
3) Student

All protected routes require JWT token in header

üöÄ Installation Guide

Prerequisites
Node.js (v16 or higher)
Oracle Database 19c+
SQL*Plus
Git

Step-by-Step Setup

üöÄ Step-by-Step Setup

‚úÖ STEP 1: Install Node.js

Download and install Node.js from:
https://nodejs.org

Verify installation:
node -v
npm -v

‚úÖ STEP 2: Install Oracle SQL

Install Oracle Database and ensure it is running properly.

‚úÖ STEP 3: Open SQL Plus

Launch SQL Plus and login as a privileged user (like SYSTEM).

üë§ Create Database User
CREATE USER testuser IDENTIFIED BY test123;
GRANT CONNECT, RESOURCE TO testuser;

üîê Connect to the User
CONNECT testuser/test123@localhost:1521/FREEPDB1;

üóÑÔ∏è Create Tables
CREATE TABLE USERS (
    ID NUMBER GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,
    USERNAME VARCHAR2(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    PASSWORD VARCHAR2(255) NOT NULL,
    ROLE VARCHAR2(50) NOT NULL
);

üë• Insert Default Users

-> Add this to server.js
import { seedUsers } from "./controllers/authController.js";

dotenv.config();
await connectDB();
checkTwilioAccountStatus();
seedUsers();

‚öôÔ∏è Backend Configuration
‚úÖ STEP 4: Create .env File

Inside the backend folder, create a file named .env and add your credentials:

STEP 5: cd backend
npm install
node server.js

STEP 6: cd frontend
npx react-scripts start
npm start

üìå Notes

Ensure Oracle Database service is running before starting the backend.
Do not expose your .env file in public repositories.
Use .gitignore to exclude sensitive files.

‚úÖ Setup Complete!

.env
ORACLE_USER=
ORACLE_PASSWORD=
ORACLE_CONNECT_STRING=

TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=

FRONTEND_URL=

BACKEND_URL=
PORT=

NODE_ENV=
JWT_SECRET=

